summary: This is a travel authorization notification for a DOJ employee to travel to Stockholm, Sweden from February 3-6, 2020, for the purpose of conducting witness interviews related to the Epstein investigation (case reference 2018R01618). The authorization was approved on January 24, 2020, and is pending further approval.

events.title: Planned Witness Interviews in Stockholm
events.description: A DOJ employee is authorized to travel to Stockholm, Sweden to conduct witness interviews for the Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: The DOJ was actively investigating the Epstein case as of early 2020, with case reference 2018R01618.
Witness interviews were planned in Stockholm, Sweden from February 3-6, 2020.
The travel authorization was approved on January 24, 2020, and was pending further approval at the time of the notification.
The document indicates international investigative activity related to the Epstein case.
